Mxolisi Mngadi, News24Police search and rescue. (Supplied, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A British triathlete drowned while swimming at a Durban beach on Friday morning, KwaZulu-Natal police said.Dave Lewiston, 79, drowned at Oasis Beach, near the Moses Mabhida Stadium, Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said. He was swimming in the shore break after cycling on the beach's promenade when he drowned. He regularly visited SA to train for triathlons. Durban police search and rescue unit divers recovered his body. An inquest docket was opened at Durban Central SAPS. His next of kin in Australia has been notified. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.